detailed_results.question: What is the maximum AC interrupting rating for the Siemens 3VA41 circuit breaker at 480VAC?
retrieved_docs: NOARK - Power Circuit Breakers and Non-Automatic Switches - A32 ASD32 - Datasheet.pdf
detailed_results.answer:
The maximum AC interrupting rating for the Siemens 3VA41 circuit breaker at 480VAC is 65kA [3].

Specifically, for 3VA41 3-Pole thermal-magnetic trip circuit breakers, the H-Interrupting Class (HEAB) has an interrupting rating of 65 kA at 480V AC (50/60 Hz) [1][2]. This is also stated as "65,000" Amperes for the 3VA41 HEAB under UL / 480V ratings [4].

judgment.explanation: The RAG system provides the correct answer (65kA) and elaborates on the different interrupting classes (H-Interrupting Class) and their corresponding ratings. It is faithful to the retrieved context and provides relevant information in a clear and well-structured manner.
